description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for the appointment of Theatre Practitioners within our In-Patient Theatre department at Torbay Hospital. We are looking for experienced and / or newly qualified practitioners who are either NMC or HCPC registered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate about delivering the highest standards of care within a team of caring and committed professionals, then this is the position for you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 10 in-patient theatres providing a range of clinical specialities including obs &amp; gynae, breast, urology, ENT, max-fax, vascular, Colo-rectal, upper GI, trauma &amp; orthopaedics. We also have a forward-thinking anaesthetic department which provides a range of services around the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer excellent continued personal development. We have a superb educational facility on site where we cater for a vast range of developmental activities in an environment where learning thrives. We also have department practice educators who will support you in your learning and development needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this exciting opportunity and would like further information, or would like to arrange an informal visit please contact Principal ODP Dave Brown on 01803 655464 or by email david.brown12@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note if you are a newly qualified practitioners with either the NMC or HCPC body and are pending your pin, please tick “YES” to have a professional registration. Please state in your supporting information that you are pending your pin with X professional body.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
